-- MORE: JPMorgan Sees Japan Revising Up 2Q GDP Growth to 3.6% Q/Q
-- B y   A n d y   S h a r p
-- 2013-09-02T03:23:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-02/more-jpmorgan-sees-japan-revising-up-2q-gdp-growth-to-3-6-q-q.html
Masamichi Adachi, senior economist
at JPMorgan Chase & Co. in  Tokyo  and a former BOJ official,
writes in e-mailed note after release of capital spending data.
* Annualized 2Q GDP growth will likely be revised up to 3.6%
from preliminary reading of 2.6%: JPMorgan
* NOTE: Revised 2Q GDP data due Sept. 9
* 2Q capital spending was unchanged Y/y, compared with a median
forecast of economists for 2.1% fall: NSN MSH10T6S972C <GO>
* “A sales-tax increase isn’t a done deal, revised GDP is just
one element feeding into the decision,": Adachi says in
telephone interview
* NOTE: Govt will look at revised GDP and other economic data
when deciding whether to go ahead with a planned increase in a
sales tax: NSN MSG20R6JTSEE <GO>
* Economists from banks including HSBC Holdings Plc. and UBS AG
also see an upward revision to 2Q GDP
* ‘‘The trend for business investment is overall positive,":
Izumi Devalier, Japan economist at HSBC in  Hong Kong , says in e-mail
